      <p>
        In the summer I like to go magnet fishing. Low effort, weirdly
        satisfying. Feels like a treasure hunt, especially with friends.
      </p>

      <p>
        I read books, watch movies and shows ‚Äî mostly sci-fi, thrillers, anime.
        I used to play guitar more often; it still comes out now and then.
      </p>

      <p>
        Hiking, puzzles, jogging ‚Äî the list goes on. I won‚Äôt pretend I do them
        all regularly, but they‚Äôre all there.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="about-visual">
      <svg
        class="about-svg"
        viewBox="0 0 120 120"
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
      >
        <circle cx="30" cy="30" r="30" fill="var(--accent)"></circle>
        <circle
          cx="80"
          cy="80"
          r="20"
          fill="var(--color-bg)"
          stroke="var(--accent)"
          stroke-width="6"></circle>
        <path
          d="M 0 100 Q 60 60 120 100"
          stroke="var(--accent)"
          stroke-width="5"
          fill="none"></path>
      </svg>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="about-section reverse">
    <div class="about-text">
      <h2>üß† Tech & Tinkering</h2>

      <p>
        I started coding early ‚Äî when websites still used table layouts and
        blinking text. First projects were in pure HTML and CSS, and I built
        little games with CoolBasic. None of them survived. I kind of wish they
        did.
      </p>

      <p>
        I'm into tech history: things like ‚Äúwhy VHS beat Betamax‚Äù or ‚Äúwhat
