        systems and decisions mix.
      </p>

      <p>
        I've messed around with different OSes, run a home Linux server, and
        started countless side projects. Many based on a joke. Most unfinished.
        Fun while they lasted.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="about-visual">
      <svg
        class="about-svg"
        viewBox="0 0 120 120"
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
      >
        <rect x="10" y="10" width="40" height="40" fill="var(--accent)"></rect>
        <rect
          x="60"
          y="60"
          width="50"
          height="50"
          fill="none"
          stroke="var(--accent)"
          stroke-width="5"
          rx="10"></rect>
        <line
          x1="10"
          y1="110"
          x2="110"
          y2="10"
          stroke="var(--accent)"
          stroke-width="4"></line>
      </svg>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="about-section">
    <div class="about-text">
      <h2>üß≠ What I Value</h2>

      <p>
        I like figuring things out ‚Äî in tech, people, systems, stories. I like
        weird ideas, and I think the best way to learn is by trying things out.
      </p>

      <p>
        I admire people who are genuinely into things. Doesn‚Äôt matter what:
        jazz, insects, obscure programming languages. Passion is cool.
      </p>
      <p>
        If any of this feels familiar, you‚Äôll probably enjoy my <a href="/blog"
          >blog</a
        >.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="about-visual">
      <svg
        class="about-svg"
        viewBox="0 0 120 120"
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
      >
        <circle cx="60" cy="60" r="25" fill="var(--accent)"></circle>
        <line
          x1="60"
          y1="0"
          x2="60"
          y2="120"
          stroke="var(--accent)"
          stroke-width="4"></line>
        <line
          x1="0"
          y1="60"
          x2="120"
          y2="60"
          stroke="var(--accent)"
          stroke-width="4"></line>
      </svg>
    </div>
  </div>

  <style>
    .about-section {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      align-items: start;
      gap: 4rem;
      margin-bottom: 6rem;
    }

    .about-section.reverse {
      direction: rtl;
    }

    .about-section.reverse > * {
      direction: ltr;
    }

    .about-text {
      max-width: 65ch;
    }

    .about-visual {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
      align-items: center;
      min-height: 100%;
      height: 100%;
    }

    .about-svg {
      width: 120px;
      height: 120px;
    }

    @media (max-width: 720px) {
      .about-section,
      .about-section.reverse {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        direction: ltr;
      }

      .about-visual {
        margin-top: 0rem;
        min-height: auto;
        height: auto;
      }
    }

    .about-svg {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(20px) scale(0.95);
      transition: all 0.6s ease-out;
    }

    .about-svg.visible {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0) scale(1);
    }
  </style>
</Layout>

<script>
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
    (entries) => {
      entries.forEach((entry) => {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
          entry.target.classList.add("visible");
        }
      });
    },
    {
      threshold: 0.6,
    }
  );

  document.querySelectorAll(".about-svg").forEach((el) => {
    observer.observe(el);
  });
</script>
